Key Match Events: Kyle Higashioka hit a solo home run in the second inning, starting a five-run rally.
Manny Machado added a two-run double with the bases loaded.
Jackson Merrill followed with a two-run triple.
Jorge Soler hit a solo homer in the fifth.
Michael Harris II had a two-run shot in the eighth.
Post-Match Reflections: The Padres head up Interstate 5 to face Shohei Ohtani and the NL West rival and top-seeded Los Angeles Dodgers in a National League Division Series beginning Saturday evening at Dodger Stadium.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The sellout crowd of 47,705 — the largest in Petco Park history — roared.
Fried and Padres starter Joe Musgrove exited early with injuries.
Robert Suarez pitched a perfect ninth for the save.
Musgrove said he was going to do everything he can to come back despite the elbow issue.
Higashioka became the first Padres catcher to homer in consecutive playoff games.
